title.rendered: Pro Kabaddi 2023: Dates, Schedule, Format, Venues, Prize Money, Squads, Live Streaming, and More About PKL 10.

content.rendered:
Pro Kabaddi League 2023 is set to kick off with a match between Gujarat Giants and Telugu Titans in Ahmedabad on Saturday, December 2. The league will consist of 132 league matches played across 12 cities in India. Pawan Sehrawat emerged as the most expensive player, being picked by Telugu Titans for a whopping Rs 2.60 crore.

Schedule and Format: The pro kabaddi league stage will run until February 21, with matches starting at 7:30 PM IST. Playoffs include two eliminators, two semifinals, and the final, with the schedule to be announced later.

Teams and Venues: The 12 participating teams are Bengal Warriors, Bengaluru Bulls, Dabang Delhi K.C., Gujarat Giants, Haryana Steelers, Jaipur Pink Panthers, Patna Pirates, Puneri Paltan, U Mumba, U.P. Yoddhas, Telugu Titans, and Tamil Thalaivas. The league will follow a 12-city caravan format, starting in Ahmedabad and moving to each franchise’s home city in the specified order.

Venues: Matches will be held in Ahmedabad, Bengaluru, Pune, Chennai, Noida, Mumbai, Jaipur, Hyderabad, Patna, Delhi, Kolkata, and Panchkula.

Prize Money: The prize money for Pro Kabaddi League 2023 is yet to be disclosed. Last season, Jaipur Pink Panthers received Rs 3,00,00,000 as the winning team, while Puneri Paltan, the runners-up, got Rs 1,80,00,000.

Live Telecast and Streaming: Star Sports Network will broadcast the matches live in India, and all games will be available for streaming on the Disney+ Hotstar app and website.

Full Squads:

 Bengal Warriors Team
  • Raiders (19 players): Maninder Singh, Shrikant Jadhav, Suyog Baban Gaikar, Prashant Kumar, Aslam Saja Mohamed Thambi, Akshay Jaywant Bodake, Vishwas S, Chai-Ming Chang, Nitin Kumar, R Guhan, Maharudra Garje.
  • Defenders: Shubham Shinde, Vaibhav Bhausaheb Garje, Aditya S. Shinde, Akshay Kumar, Shreyas Umbardand, Dipak Arjun Shinde.
  • All-rounders: Nitin Rawal, Bhoir Akshay Bharat.
  • Total Players in the squad: 19
 Bengaluru Bulls Team
  • Raiders (25 players): Bharat, Vikash Kandola, Neeraj Narwal, Monu, Abhishek Singh, Sushil, Banty, Piotr Pamulak, Akshit.
  • Defenders: Aman, Saurabh Nandal, Yash Hooda, Surjeet Singh, Vishal, Ankit, Parteek, Sunder, Rakshith, Rohit Kumar, Ponparthiban Subramanian, Md. Liton Ali, Arulnanthababu, Aditya Shankar Powar.
  • All-rounders: Sachin Narwal, and Ran Singh.
  • Total Players in the squad: 25

  • Raiders: Ashu Malik, Naveen Kumar, Ashish Narwal, Suraj Panwar, Manjeet, Meetu, Manu.
  • Defenders: Vijay, Vishal Bhardwaj, Sunil, Nitin Chandel, Balasaheb Shahaji Jadhav, Felix Li, Yuvraj Pandeya, Mohit, Vikrant, Ashish, Himmat Antil, Yogesh.
